**Step P2 — Update `monitor/status.json`** with `last_analyst_run: <ISO-TS>` and `last_analyst_mode: <mode-list>`. Use `${WORKSPACE}/monitor/status.json` (FUSE-canonical) to match the rest of the pipeline.

**Step P3 — Release active-claim file (PROP-044, every run, every mode).** If this run wrote a Mode-1 claim at workstart (i.e., MODE1_RUN_ID is set), clear the FUSE active-claim file to the 'released' state. Always safe to run unconditionally — if no claim was written this run, the read-then-conditional-write is a no-op.

```bash
WORKSPACE=$(find /sessions/*/mnt/dome-model-review -maxdepth 0 2>/dev/null | head -1)
CLAIM_FILE="${WORKSPACE}/monitor/analyst/active-claim.json"
node -e "
const fs=require('fs');
const path='${CLAIM_FILE}';
let cur={};
try{cur=JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(path,'utf8'));}catch(e){}
const myRunId=process.env.MODE1_RUN_ID;
// Only clear if we are the current holder OR the file is already empty/released.
if(!cur.run_id || cur.run_id===myRunId){
  const obj={
    schema_version:'v1',
    run_id:null,
    agent:null,
    claimed_at:null,
    expires_at:null,
    released_at:new Date().toISOString(),
    released_by_run_id: myRunId||cur.run_id||null,
    last_claim_mode: cur.mode||null
  };
  fs.writeFileSync(path, JSON.stringify(obj,null,2));
  console.log('postlude P3: released active-claim');
} else {
  console.log('postlude P3: active-claim held by '+cur.run_id+' (not ours, '+myRunId+'); leaving in place');
}
"
```

Note: Step P3 deliberately does NOT delete the file (FUSE cannot unlink). It writes the released state, which subsequent prelude reads interpret as 'no active claim' via the run_id===null check.

